  "body": "It looks like every recursive call to ProcessRequirementsEnabled (pkg/chartutil/requirements.go) on a subchart ignores tags/conditions defined in the parent chart\r\n\r\nthe way to reproduce this problem: \r\n\r\n1.  parent-chart \r\n  - `tags.standalone = false`\r\n  - `requirements.dependencies: kafka`\r\n  2.  charts/subchartA\r\n    -  `requirements.dependencies: kafka (tags: standalone)`\r\n  3.  charts/subchartB\r\n    - `requirements.dependencies: kafka (tags: standalone)`\r\n\r\nIn this scenario all 3 kafka dependencies remain enabled. The required result, which is only kafka dependency of the parent chart is enabled, is achieved only when using --set tags.standalone=false explicitly in the command line. ",
